Shawn Mkhize’s son Andile needs no introduction to Mzansi people. Andile Mpisane is known for living a flashy and flamboyant life. He’s also the chairman of the Royal AM football club and also a musician. Recently, the 21-year-old showed off his fleet of expensive cars, which included a Maybach that costs about R3 million, a Rolls-Royce Cullinan worth around R13 million and a McLaren GT with a prize tag of around R4,5 million.  He also caused a frenzy on Twitter after rapper Cassper Nyovest claimed his McLaren GT was the only one in Mzansi, after which Andile posted a photo of his gold GT. Mpisane is at again but this time, he showed off his BMW I8, along with his R4,5 million McLaren. The I8 Roadster is one of Beemer’s highly prized coupes, it costs about R2,2 million for a 2022 model. A post shared by Andile Mpisane (@andilempisane10)  The new BMW i8 Coupe accelerates from 0 to 100 km/h in 4,4 seconds, while the new BMW i8 Roadster accelerates from 0 to 100 km/h in 4,6 seconds. Both models have an electronically limited top speed of 250 km/h. Hybrid-specific all-wheel drive, precision-tuned chassis.